import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of ages in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['age'] = pd.to_numeric(data['age'], errors='coerce')
    avg_age = data['age'].mean()
    plt.axvline(avg_age, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Age: {avg_age:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average age of people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['height'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20)
    plt.axvline(data['height'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Mean: {data['height'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average height of people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Height (cm)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

    plt.xlabel('Age')

    plt.title('Is there any correlation between age and height in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
